Program: Outlook
Title: 28/09/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00k9jrp
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 29 Sep 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, wedding bells ring in the world's largest refugee camp - we hear from a 24-year-old Somali woman who has grown up in Dadaab refugee camp in northern Kenya and is now about to get married. Also, we hear from the Arab bloggers learning how to avoid detection by state security services. And, the Scottish woman hailed as Britain's best answer to street violence tells us what drives her to stand up to the gangs. Show less